Ask HN: As a tech person, do you feel Google gives you better results?
text:
I have read a lot of (well-deserved IMO) hate about Google's ever shittier SERPs (Search Engine Results Pages) in the past few years. I noticed the same effect myself: the ads filling the viewport entirely, and becoming more and more indistinguishable from organic links.

However I noticed a new trend in the past few weeks. My results to technical queries got... actually quite good (like, 2010-good).

I just typed "Elixir date sigil", and got:

- 0 ads,

- 10 perfectly related pages about how Elixir (the programming language) handles dates.

Same for a lot of other queries. I have to say, it felt very good, like seeing an good friend again after having lost sight of him for years.

Have you experienced the same? Do you think Google might be afraid of losing its technical users to competition, and finally provide good results again?

Edit: formatting

Ask HN: Cool and Useful Dockerized Apps?
text:
Recently seeing this testing mailserver linked on HN: https://tweedegolf.nl/en/blog/86/introducing-mailcrab

I was reminded of another useful tool, mimic3 by MycroftAI that gives you very nice TTS: https://github.com/MycroftAI/mimic3

So I was wondering: what other useful apps have been containerized for easy setup and great usefulness?

Basically the point of this question is to let people share these, for the benefit of all.
